  "instructions": [
    "Heat the butter in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the lamb and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the red wine and beef broth and bring to a boil.",
    "Add the browned lamb, salt, black pepper, and cornstarch and stir to combine.",
    "Cover the pot and simmer for 1 hour, or until the lamb is tender.",
    "Mix in the almond butter, white vinegar, pickled red onion, parsley, and dill.",
    "Simmer for an additional 10 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened.",
    "Stir in the flour and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with parsley and paprika.",
    "Refrigerate leftovers for up to 3 days or freeze for up to 2 months."
